For static data you can set [`extra_context`][1] on the view (Django 2.0+)

    class HomePageView(TemplateView):
        template_name = &#39;home.html&#39;

        extra_context = {&#39;page_name&#39;: &#39;home&#39;}

For dynamic data or older versions of Django, you can override [`get_context_data`][2].

    import random

    class HomePageView(TemplateView):
        template_name = &#39;home.html&#39;

        def get_context_data(self, **kwargs):
            context = super().get_context_data(**kwargs)
            context[&#39;number&#39;] = random.randrange(1, 100)
            return context

[1]: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.2/ref/class-based-views/mixins-simple/#django.views.generic.base.ContextMixin.extra_context
[2]: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.2/ref/class-based-views/mixins-simple/#django.views.generic.base.ContextMixin.get_context_data

