    {$sort: {fk: 1}}

then grouping with

    {$group: {_id: &quot;$fk&quot;, ... }}, 

will be a wasted effort. 

----------

But there is a *silver lining* with sorting before `$group` stage with `name: -1`. Since you are using [`$push`][2] (not an [`$addToSet`][3]), inserted objects will retain the order they&#39;ve had in the newly created `items` array in the `$group` result. You can see this behaviour [here (copy of your pipeline)][4]

The `items` array will ***always*** have;

    &quot;items&quot;: [
      {
        ..
        &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Michael&quot;
      },
      {
        ..
        &quot;name&quot;: &quot;George&quot;
      }
    ]

in same order, therefore your nested array sort is a *non-issue*! Though I am unable to find an exact quote in documentation to confirm this behaviour, you can check;

- [this](http://hudsonburgess.com/2017/01/04/mongodb-first-doc-by-group.html),
- or [this](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/18242953/mongodb-aggregation-framework-group-and-sort) where it is confirmed.
- Also, [accumulator operator list][5] for `$group`, where `$addToSet` has `&quot;Order of the array elements is undefined.&quot;` in its description, whereas the similar operator `$push` does not, which might be an indirect evidence? :)

Just a simple modification of your pipeline where you move the `fk: 1` sort from pre-`$group` stage to post-`$group` stage;

    db.getCollection(&#39;col1&#39;).aggregate([
        {$match: {fk: {$in: [1, 2]}}},
        {$sort: {name: -1}},
        {$group: {_id: &quot;$fk&quot;, items: {$push: &quot;$$ROOT&quot;} }},
        {$sort: {_id: 1}},
        {$project: {items: {$slice: [&quot;$items&quot;, 2]} }}
    ])

should be sufficient to have the main result array order fixed as well. Check it on [mongoplayground](https://mongoplayground.net/p/0Qd2j6i-iVB)


  [1]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/group/
  [2]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/push/#grp._S_push
  [3]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/addToSet/#grp._S_addToSet
  [4]: https://mongoplayground.net/p/dLQ5KHgTpHr
  [5]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/group/#accumulator-operator

